column1: Wind Wave Tank Transfer Function Input - Output Sheet

The blue cells are user input or specified cells, white are calculation cells and green our inputs for the wavemaker program.  The white and green cells will auto-populate once you have specified whether you are inputing Period or Frequency, the desired Time Value and Desired Amplitude.

If a specified wave period/frequency falls within the Deep or Shallow Water regime, the Actual Wave Length column will specify the correct calculated wave length.  If the Actual Wave Length column reads exactly "1000" mm, then the wave falls into the Intermediate Water Depth regime and the Goal Seek Function must be used to calculate the recursive formula for wave length.  In the Data page, go to the What-If Analysis dropdown and select Goal Seek...  From there set the following condtions:
Set Cell: to be the Itteraged Formula for Intermediatae Water cell.
By changing cell: to be the Intermediate Water Wave Length cell.
